cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with the problem of computing isocontours in road networks, which involves graph theory and computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes heuristics for solving the problem, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of minimum-link paths in simple polygons suggests the relevance of cs.GR (Computer Graphics) as well. Finally, the practical application of the algorithms in road networks implies the relevance of cs.RO (Robotics).
